  "issue_title": "genie-ctl ignores `[core].port` and `bind_host` \u2014 always connects to `127.0.0.1:3000`",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`genie-ctl` hardcodes the genie-core HTTP base URL as `127.0.0.1:3000` and does not read `[core].port` or `[core].bind_host` from `geniepod.toml`, even when `GENIEPOD_CONFIG` is set. CLI commands such as `chat`, `health`, `tools`, and `history` fail or report false negatives when genie-core runs on a non-default port.\n\n## Current behavior\n\n- Set a non-default port in config, for example in `geniepod.toml`:\n\n  ```toml\n  [core]\n  port = 3001\n  bind_host = \"127.0.0.1\"\n  ```\n\n- Start genie-core with that config:\n\n  ```bash\n  GENIEPOD_CONFIG=/path/to/geniepod.toml ./target/release/genie-core\n  ```\n\n- Verify the API is up on the configured port:\n\n  ```bash\n  curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:3001/api/health\n  ```\n\n- Run genie-ctl with the same config:\n\n  ```bash\n  GENIEPOD_CONFIG=/path/to/geniepod.toml genie-ctl chat \"what time is it?\"\n  ```\n\n- Result:\n\n  ```text\n  Error: Connection refused (os error 111)\n  ```\n\n- `genie-ctl version` always prints:\n\n  ```text\n  core: 127.0.0.1:3000\n  ```\n\n- `genie-ctl health` reports `[DOWN] genie-core` even when genie-core is healthy on the configured port.\n\n- Direct API calls to the configured port still work:\n\n  ```bash\n  curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:3001/api/chat \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d '{\"message\":\"what time is it?\"}'\n  ```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n- `genie-ctl` should resolve the genie-core base URL from loaded config: `{bind_host}:{port}` (respecting `GENIEPOD_CONFIG` and default `/etc/geniepod/geniepod.toml`).\n- All HTTP subcommands (`chat`, `health`, `tools`, `history`, `search`, `conversations`, `connectivity`, `support-bundle`, diagnostics) should target the configured core endpoint.\n- `genie-ctl version` should display the resolved core URL, not a hardcoded default.\n- When genie-core is unreachable at the configured address, errors should reference that URL.\n\n## Context\n\n`genie-core` correctly honors `[core].port` and `[core].bind_host`. `genie-ctl` already calls `Config::load()` for some commands (for example speaker enrollment) but uses `const CORE_URL: &str = \"127.0.0.1:3000\"` for all core HTTP traffic in `crates/genie-ctl/src/main.rs`.\n\nThis breaks local development when running multiple instances, using a non-default port to avoid conflicts, or matching Jetson deployments that change the core port behind a gateway.\n\nRelated prior work ([PR #40](https://github.com/GeniePod/genie-claw/pull/40)) made `genie-ctl health` use `/api/health` for backend-neutral LLM status; it did not wire the core host/port from config.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- With `port = 3001` (and default `bind_host`), `genie-ctl chat`, `health`, `tools`, and `history` succeed when genie-core is listening on `127.0.0.1:3001`.\n- With `GENIEPOD_CONFIG` unset, behavior on the default port (`3000`) is unchanged.\n- `genie-ctl version` shows the resolved core URL from config.\n- `genie-ctl health` reports genie-core as up when `/api/health` on the configured endpoint returns success.\n- No regression for governor socket and other non-HTTP commands.",
